COMMENT ON TABLE PROGRAM_SERVICES IS 'Defines every program that can be delivered through the programs and services module, of any category, including program phases and modules.';
COMMENT ON COLUMN PROGRAM_SERVICES.PROGRAM_ID IS 'An internal unique identifier of the program.';
COMMENT ON COLUMN PROGRAM_SERVICES.PARENT_PROGRAM_ID IS 'For programs made up of phases and modules: the parent program of the accredited program to which the phase belongs. An accredited program can consist of multiple phases similar to courses in a curriculum. Each phase is stored as its own record, and linked to the main accredited program.';
COMMENT ON COLUMN PROGRAM_SERVICES.ACTIVE_FLAG IS 'A flag (Y/N) to indicate whether the program is active.';
COMMENT ON COLUMN PROGRAM_SERVICES.DESCRIPTION IS 'The description of the program or service.';
COMMENT ON COLUMN PROGRAM_SERVICES.PROGRAM_CLASS IS 'Identifies if the record is a parent program or a child module / phase / block within a parent accredited program. System populated as PRG (program), PRG_MOD (program module), PRG_BLK (program block), PRG_PH (program phase). Ref Domain ( PRG_CLS )';
COMMENT ON COLUMN PROGRAM_SERVICES.BREAK_ALLOWED_FLAG IS 'For accredited programs (module_flag = Y): indicates whether a break can be scheduled between modules.';
COMMENT ON COLUMN PROGRAM_SERVICES.CAPACITY IS 'The recommended maximum number of offenders for this program. Applied as default capacity for provider offerings of this program.';
COMMENT ON COLUMN PROGRAM_SERVICES.COMMENT_TEXT IS 'Free text notes associated with this program / service.';
COMMENT ON COLUMN PROGRAM_SERVICES.COMPLETION_FLAG IS 'For accredited programs: For reporting purposes, indicates if offender completion of this module means the entire program has been successfully completed. Imposes no business rules on the system, only used for reporting.';
COMMENT ON COLUMN PROGRAM_SERVICES.CONTACT_METHOD IS 'Method of contact in free text. No longer used.';
COMMENT ON COLUMN PROGRAM_SERVICES.END_DATE IS 'No longer used.';
COMMENT ON COLUMN PROGRAM_SERVICES.EXPIRY_DATE IS 'The date on which the program or service became inactive.';
COMMENT ON COLUMN PROGRAM_SERVICES.FUNCTION_TYPE IS 'Integration point with the workflow module. Defines (for community programs) the team function that will provide this program. (For community programs, internal providers are Teams rather than agency locations). For each team, each Function defines a job or activity that team performs. Defining a Function on a program means that this program can be provided by a Team with the same Function.';
COMMENT ON COLUMN PROGRAM_SERVICES.LIST_SEQ IS 'Configurable listing order for pick lists.';
COMMENT ON COLUMN PROGRAM_SERVICES.MODULE_FLAG IS 'For records where program_class = PRG_PH only: indicates (Y/N) if this phase has a modular structure (for scheduling purposes).';
COMMENT ON COLUMN PROGRAM_SERVICES.MODULE_TYPE IS 'For records where program_class = PRG_PH only, and only when module_flag = Y: Indicates the type of modular structure (for scheduling purposes) - BLOCK, SEQUENTIAL, and ROLLING (system dependent values). Ref Domain ( PS_MOD_TYPE )';
COMMENT ON COLUMN PROGRAM_SERVICES.NO_OF_ALLOWABLE_ABSENCES IS 'For accredited programs: The total number of absences an offender is allowed before that offender''s participation must be terminated (failed to complete). No longer used.';
COMMENT ON COLUMN PROGRAM_SERVICES.NO_OF_ALLOWABLE_RESTARTS IS 'For accredited programs: the total number of times an offender is allowed to restart this program after previous unsuccessful attempts. No longer used.';
COMMENT ON COLUMN PROGRAM_SERVICES.NO_OF_SESSIONS IS 'For accredited programs: the total number of sessions required to complete this program phase / module / block. Used for generating schedules for this program. (The system generated schedule will contain exactly this number of sessions.)';
COMMENT ON COLUMN PROGRAM_SERVICES.NO_OF_WEEKLY_SESSIONS IS 'For accredited programs: for scheduling purposes, indicates the maximum recommended number of sessions per week.';
COMMENT ON COLUMN PROGRAM_SERVICES.PHASE_TYPE IS 'For accredited programs: indicates whether this phase should be held as a course (value = SESSION) or should be delivered individually (value = APPOINTMENT) to the offender. APPOINTMENT is intended for introductory phases that typically involve individual offender appointments before placement into the core program. Ref Domain ( PS_PHS_TYPE )';
COMMENT ON COLUMN PROGRAM_SERVICES.PROGRAM_CATEGORY IS 'The code used to identify the program category. The value is internally recorded to support each category of program. Values INST_ACT (institutional activities), ACP (accredited programs) and CSO (community service), and more will be added as new program category capabilities are added. Ref Domain ( PS_CATEGORY )';
COMMENT ON COLUMN PROGRAM_SERVICES.PROGRAM_CODE IS 'The code used to identify the program or service.';
COMMENT ON COLUMN PROGRAM_SERVICES.PROGRAM_STATUS IS 'For accredited programs: indicates if there is a pilot program, unaccredited or officially accredited. For information / reporting purposes only. Ref Domain ( PS_STATUS )';
COMMENT ON COLUMN PROGRAM_SERVICES.SESSION_LENGTH IS 'The session length in hours. Used for generating the end time of a generated program schedule.';
COMMENT ON COLUMN PROGRAM_SERVICES.START_DATE IS 'The start date. No longer used.';
COMMENT ON COLUMN PROGRAM_SERVICES.START_FLAG IS 'For accredited programs where module_flag = Y: Indicates whether an offender can start this accredited program at this module. (While often allowed, some modules have pre-requisites).';
COMMENT ON COLUMN PROGRAM_SERVICES.CREATE_DATETIME IS 'The timestamp when the record was created';
COMMENT ON COLUMN PROGRAM_SERVICES.CREATE_USER_ID IS 'The user account that created the record';
COMMENT ON COLUMN PROGRAM_SERVICES.MODIFY_DATETIME IS 'The timestamp when the record was last modified ';
COMMENT ON COLUMN PROGRAM_SERVICES.MODIFY_USER_ID IS 'The user account that last modified the record';
COMMENT ON COLUMN PROGRAM_SERVICES.SEAL_FLAG IS 'Flag to indicate whether the record has been sealed or not (Y/N).';
